.Dd April 23, 2026
.Dt MAT_VARSETSTRUCTFIELDBYINDEX 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm Mat_VarSetStructFieldByIndex
.Nd Sets a field in a structure array by index.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <matio.h>
.Ft matvar_t *
.Fo Mat_VarSetStructFieldByIndex
.Fa "matvar_t *matvar"
.Fa "size_t field_index"
.Fa "size_t index"
.Fa "matvar_t *field"
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn Mat_VarSetStructFieldByIndex
function assigns
.Fa field
to the structure field at 0-relative field index
.Fa field_index
for the structure element at linear
.Fa index
in
.Fa matvar .
The function requires
.Fa matvar
to be a structure variable created by
.Fn Mat_VarCreateStruct
or
.Fn Mat_VarCreateStruct2 .
When a field is assigned successfully, the field variable name is updated to
match the structure field name.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
On success, the previous field stored at the requested structure element and
field position is returned.
If no previous field was set, or if
.Fa matvar
is not a valid structure variable, NULL is returned.
.Sh EXAMPLES
This example assigns a field in a structure array by index.
.Bd -literal
matvar_t *old_field;

old_field = Mat_VarSetStructFieldByIndex(matvar, 1, 0, field2);
if ( old_field != NULL )
    Mat_VarFree(old_field);
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr Mat_VarCreateStruct 3 ,
.Xr Mat_VarCreateStruct2 3 ,
.Xr Mat_VarAddStructField 3 ,
.Xr Mat_VarSetStructFieldByName 3